  "name": "The Thing in the Reservoir",
  "format": "commander",
  "theme": "Steer the town's living pollution: every die, coin, and vote the whole table makes feeds Big Murph sludge counters until the communal kaiju is big enough to wash over every opponent at once.",
  "description": "It was the water all along. Decades of Whateverville's dumped chaos pooled in the reservoir, grew three eyes and a taste for ballots, and crawled out of the water treatment plant with a name nobody wants to say twice: Big Murph. This Gruul (RG) deck is a SHARED, ESCALATING MENACE built on the Feed mechanic — whenever ANY player anywhere at the table rolls a die, flips a coin, or votes, the monster you steer gains sludge counters and gets bigger. And it doesn't pick favorites: when the beast grows or attacks, it washes over the WHOLE table at once. You profit by steering it, but the threat is communal — the more the pod does its usual dice-and-elections thing, the more it feeds the thing in the reservoir, and property values have already started to fall. An acorn (Un-set) Commander deck with chaos kept deliberately LOW — almost-functional toxic-mutant Gruul thinning to a handful of chaos-5 fever-dreams. Color-identity and singleton rules are waived for acorn decks.",
  "artDirection": "Whateverville's poisoned reservoir and crumbling water-treatment plant: toxic runoff, rusted pipes and concrete reclaimed by mutant overgrowth, bubbling sludge and drifting litter under a bruised stormy sky. Gruul palette of murky green, rust red, and sickly bioluminescence. Mood: toxic ecological menace swelling up out of the muck.",
